    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-09-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="56" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                <head>No. 56.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Putnam</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-09-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 7,
                            1880</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 13.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: A note has been received from the chargé
                        d’affaires <hi rend="italic">ad interim</hi> of Belgium in this country,
                        conveying an invitation to this government to nominate one or more delegates
                        to attend the international congress of commerce and industry which
                        assembles this month at Brussels. No provision having been made by Congress
                        to meet the invitation by a direct appointment associated with compensation,
                        I have simply to state that you will be and are hereby authorized to take
                        part in the proposed congress (at your own discretion) in sufficient
                        representation of the United States, and to associate with you therein Mr.
                        Wilson, consul at Brussels, should he consent. If preferred, Mr. Wilson can
                        act as the sole delegate.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
